
SPECC     : Converts frequency representation to spectral centroid.

     This command translates frequency inputs to a corresponding spectral
     centroid (i.e. the amplitude weighted center frequency of a spectrum).

Inputs processed:

     **freq,    **specC

Syntax:

     specc [-p n] [-x] [inputfile ...]

Options:

     -p n   : set output precision to n decimal places
     -x     : suppress outputting of non-specC data

  Refer to reference manual for further details.

